Oct 07, 2021
SoundID Privacy Policy
INTRODUCTION
In this SoundID Privacy Policy (“Privacy Policy”), Sonarworks SIA (“Sonarworks” or “we”), informs you (“you”) about the processing of personal data for which we are responsible in the sense of the applicable legislation, including the General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”).
We consider the protection of your privacy and personal data as an important business value. Therefore, we only process your personal data in accordance with this Privacy Policy, and applicable law, including the GDPR.
In the Privacy Policy, we describe why and how we collect and process personal data related to the use of our website, mobile application, online purchases of SoundID software products, and the use of the trial version of our software.
Personal data is any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person. An identifiable natural person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identifier, such as a name, a personal identification number, location data, an online identifier, or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity of that natural person.
When we use “you” or “your” in this Privacy Policy, we are referring to the relevant individual who is the subject of the personal data.
WEBSITE VISITORS AND MOBILE APPLICATION USERS
Each time you access us online, we collect the following information about the device you are using: IP address, the request from your browser, the date and time of this request, as well as the status and amount of data transferred by the request. We also collect information about the browser used, the operating system of the device and the Internet service provider.
This data is collected automatically, including via the use of cookies and other tracking technologies when you visit our website.
Cookies are small text files that are dropped on a user’s web browser by the website that the user is viewing. Each cookie contains a small amount of information, such as a unique identifier that links the user to a specific website. Our website may use cookies to track the number of times you have visited the website, to track the number of visitors to the website, to determine and analyze visitors’ use of our websites, to store data that you provide (such as your preferences), and to store technical information related to your interactions with our website. We may also use session cookies, which are deleted when you close your browser, to store your user ID, to facilitate your movement around our websites (particularly in connection with information searches and order placement), and other information used in administering the session.
You can find out more about our use of cookies in our Cookie Policy.
If you use our website without revealing your identity or without providing any personal data, the processing of the above-mentioned information is not considered as processing of personal data within the meaning of the GDPR. If, on the other hand, you perform activities on our website that require the provision of identifiable personal data, we process your data for the purposes and on the legal basis described below.
The purpose of the above-mentioned data processing is to enable appropriate operation of our website, to enable the content of our website to be displayed on your device, to detect and eliminate errors, to determine how our website are used, to make adjustments and improvements to our products, our website, and to personalize your browsing experience by displaying content that is more likely to be relevant and of interest to you.
The legal basis for processing your personal data for the above-mentioned purposes is our legitimate interests, namely, the demand-oriented design of the website, and the provision of network and information security.
REGISTRATION FOR A USER ACCOUNT
You can sign up for the use of our SoundID mobile application (“App”)as a user of our website offers and. To do that, you will need to enter your name and email address, or link your SoundID account with a third-party online account you may have. We also record and process the date and time of registration and the IP address. By registering for use of our App, you are giving your explicit consent to process your personal data according to the purpose stated below.
The purpose of the processing of this data is to offer a personalized service, conduct quality and risk management and to prevent unauthorized access to restricted areas of the website or restricted content.
The legal basis for the processing of your data for registration is your consent. If you register for the initiation or fulfilment of a contract with us, the legal basis for the processing of your data is also the performance of a contract or the steps taken prior to entering into a contract.
CREATING A SOUNDID PROFILE ON THE APP
To enjoy the advantages of SoundID, you will need to create a SoundID profile. While creating your SoundID profile, you will be asked to enter your gender, age and indicate the type of headphones used. By providing this personal data, you are giving your explicit consent to the processing of it for the purpose stated below.
The purpose of the processing of this personal data is to analyze the sound preferences of the users of our App, depending on their age and gender, and the type of headphones used in order to offer a sound setting that improves your listening experience.
The legal basis for the processing of your data for registration is your consent. If you register for the initiation or fulfilment of a contract with us, the legal basis for the processing of your data is also the performance of a contract or the steps taken prior to entering into a contract.
When you use the App, we collect personal data on your sound preferences, including the duration and the frequency of your listening.
You have the right to object to the processing of your above-mentioned personal data at any time by sending an email to: soundid@sonarworks.com.
The purpose of the processing of this personal data is to determine and analyze the sound preferences of the users of the App in order to customize and personalize our products.
Sonarworks does not process data on your sound preferences for marketing purposes and in no circumstances transfers information on your listening habits to third parties.
The legal basis for the processing of your listening habits is our legitimate interests, namely, to improve our software through adapting it to the listeners’ preferences.
THIRD-PARTY TRACKING AND ONLINE ADVERTISING
We may permit third-party ad networks, social media companies, and other third-party services to collect information about browsing behavior from the visitors of our websites through cookies, social plug-ins, or other tracking technology. We may permit third-party online advertising networks to collect information about your use of our websites over time, so that they may play or display ads that may be relevant to your interests on our services, as well as on other websites or services (“interest-based advertising”). Typically, the information is collected through cookies or similar tracking technologies.
For example, we use tracking technologies from traffic measurement services, such as Google Analytics, to analyze traffic and for analytics purposes, and the Facebook Custom Audience customer remarketing feature to allow you to receive interest-based advertisements as part of your Facebook visit.
You may exercise choices regarding receipt of interest-based advertising by submitting opt-outs. Some of the advertisers and service providers that perform advertising-related services for us and our partners participate in the Digital Advertising Alliance (“DAA”) Self-Regulatory Program for Online Behavioral Advertising. To learn more about how you can exercise certain choices regarding interest-based advertising, visit
https://optout.aboutads.info/
.
You may exercise choices regarding the use of cookies from Reddit by visiting
https://www.reddit.com/personalization/
.
Please be aware that, even if you are able to opt out of certain kinds of interest-based advertising, you may continue to receive other types of ads. Opting out only means that those selected partners should no longer deliver certain interest-based advertising to you, but does not mean you will no longer receive any targeted content and/or ads (e.g., from other ad networks). Sonarworks is not responsible for the effectiveness of, or compliance with, any third-party opt-out options or programs, or the accuracy of their statements regarding their programs.
If you have any questions about opting out of the collection of cookies and other tracking/recording tools, you can contact us directly at
soundid@sonarworks.com
.
COMMUNICATION
You can communicate with us via the request form on our website or by email. When you use one of these contact points to get in touch with us, we collect the personal data you provide us via the selected contact point. It can be your name, email address, postal address, phone number and/or the information you provide in communication with us.
The purpose of the processing of this data is to answer your question or request, to identify users who have difficulties using our products, to offer support for our products and services, as well as to analyze the nature and regularity of questions and reported issues.
The legal basis for the processing of this data is our legitimate interests, namely, to distribute actual and detailed information about our products, to summarize more frequent questions, and to identify problems and necessity for improvements of our products.
If you contact us for the initiation or fulfilment of a contract, the legal basis for the processing of your data is also the performance of a contract or the steps taken prior to entering into a contract.
NEWSLETTER
You can subscribe to our newsletter on our website or the App. When you sign up for our newsletter, your email address will be used to send you regular information on our current topics and other advertising materials. You can opt out of receiving the newsletter at any time sending an email to soundid@sonarworks.com.
The purpose of the processing of this data is to distribute the latest information about our products.
The legal basis for the processing of this data for the above-mentioned purposes is your consent, if you have explicitly subscribed to the newsletter. From time to time, you may also receive the newsletter from us without explicit consent in case you have ordered our products or services, and have not objected to receiving the information by email. In this case, the legal basis for the processing of your data is our legitimate interests to inform our clients and newsletter subscribers about our new, up-to-date and/or personalized products, as well as our services or special offers (e.g. discounts).
SOUND PREFERENCE AND HEARING TEST
Our App offers the opportunity to take a hearing and sound preference test. By choosing this option, you agree to the processing of data on your sound preferences and other data you enter in the application form, as well as your hearing threshold measurements.
The purpose of the processing of this data is to enable us to provide our product, the SoundID software, to you.
The legal basis for the processing of your personal data for the above-mentioned purposes is your consent. After you have purchased the SoundID software or chosen to use the trial version of the SoundID software, the legal basis for the processing of the above-mentioned personal data is the performance of a contract.
DATA RETENTION
We will retain your personal data collected via our website and/or App as long as it is necessary for communicating with you and for legitimate and essential business purposes, such as maintaining our products and services, making data-driven business decisions about new features and offerings, but no longer than five years.
The retention period for data collected via the use of cookies is determined in our Cookie Policy.
CUSTOMERS, POTENTIAL CUSTOMERS AND SOUNDID SOFTWARE USERS
To ensure the conclusion and performance of the contract, we may process the following personal data:
your name, phone number, email address, postal address;
computer ID (CID), IP, computer name, computer type, headphone name, headphone profile, microphone profile name, input/output device name and ID, calibration profile name;
specific information, such as student or teacher certificate, personal identification number, educational establishment where you work or study to get discounts offered by us;
payment information;
data you provide to us for the provision of our services and resolving issues;
other information you have provided to us.
The purposes of the processing of data collected prior to the conclusion or during the performance of the contract are:
providing of products and services that you have requested and performing of deliveries in accordance with the Terms and Conditions and/or the End User License Agreement (“EULA”);
communicating information that is relevant for our deliveries in particular and our customer relations in general;
processing orders, invoices, payments and performing financial follow-ups;
carrying out security activities, including the detection and prevention of security threats and malicious use of our products and services;
identifying users who have difficulties using our products;
offering support for our products and services;
carrying out quality and risk management activities;
administering, managing and developing our products and services, as well as improving the quality of our products and services by analyzing data;
informing you about our products and services that are closely related to the products and services you already use or have tried to use;
publishing your review if your consent for that has been received;
complying with legal obligations we are subject to.
The main legal basis for the processing of your personal data for the above-mentioned purposes is to take steps at your request prior to entering into a contract and to ensure the performance of the contract.
Besides that, the legal basis is also our legitimate interests, namely, to ensure security conditions, to provide quality of our products and services, and to promote our business.
The legal basis for the processing of your personal data for the above-mentioned purposes may be also your consent and the necessity to comply with legal obligations we are subject to.
DATA RETENTION
The data will be stored by us for as long as necessary to fulfil the contract, as well as for a period after the fulfillment of the contractual obligations for commercial and tax purposes. This retention period is usually 10 years after the expiration of the contract, or after the obligation under applicable law has been performed.
RECIPIENTS OF PERSONAL DATA
The primary recipient of your personal data is Sonarworks and its employees.
To be able to offer you the best possible services and remain competitive in our business, we share certain data with other organizations. As a result, personal data may be transferred outside the countries where we or the data subject is located. This includes countries outside the European Union (“EU”).
We use contractual arrangements and security mechanisms as appropriate to protect the data and to comply with applicable laws, including the GDPR.
Where we transfer personal data outside the EU to a country not determined by the European Commission as providing an adequate level of protection for personal data, the transfers will be under an agreement covering the EU requirements for the transfer of personal data outside the EU, such as the European-Commission-approved standard contractual clauses. Please contact us to receive more detailed information about our data processors.
Personal data processed by us may be transferred to third-party organizations that provide applications/functionality, data processing or IT services to us or otherwise assist us in providing goods, services or information.
We use third parties to support us in providing our services and to help provide, run and manage our internal IT systems. The third parties include, for example, providers of information technology, cloud-based software as a service (SaaS), identity management, website hosting and management, data analysis, data backup, security and storage services, as well as organizations that coordinate our marketing activities or events and manage customer communications, prepare reports and statistics, printing materials and designing products, and place advertisements on apps, websites and social media. Further details of these providers are included below.
